Try this throughout the lunar cycle! A fun activity for the whole family this holiday weekend.
When you see a full Moon, your partner (looking at you from where the golf ball Moon is) shouldn't see any light on your face: a new Earth.
If you do the activity, your head is the Earth. Have your partner watch how much of your face is illuminated, standing by the golf ball Moon
That activity will show you how we see the phases of the Moon from the Earth. Find a partner to help you think about the phases of the Earth
Convince yourself! Try an activity like this: https://t.co/du1w9NNHsH
Only from the Moon, the phases of the Earth are opposite! When you see a full Moon, I see a new Earth. If you see a 1st Qtr, I see 3rd Qtr.
That's right: from my perspective orbiting the Moon, I get to watch the Earth go through phases, just like you watch the phases of the Moon.
Full Moon tonight for all of you Earthlings, and a New Earth for me!
